Description.TranslatedText:
Date part of AESTDTC convert to numeric. 
If AESTDTC is partial or missing, apply the following imputation rule:
-If only DAY is missing: 
If the AE end date (AEENDTC) is after the date of first vaccination (ADSL.TR01SDT) or is missing AND the start month and year of the AE (AESTDTC) coincide with the start month and year of the first vaccination (ADSL.TR01SDT), use the date of first vaccination for ASTDT and time of first vaccination for ASTTM; 
Otherwise, use the first day of the month;
-If DAY and Month are both missing:
If the AE end date is after the date of first vaccination or is missing AND the start year of the AE coincides with the start year of the first vaccination, use the date of first vaccination;
Otherwise, use the first day of the year;
-If DAY, Month and Year are all missing, the date will not be imputed. "

M if year is present and month is imputed;
D if only day is imputed;
Otherwise null.

Set to 'Grade 1' if AETOXGR='1';
Set to 'Grade 2’ if AETOXGR='2';
Set to ‘Grade 3’ if AETOXGR='3';
Set to ‘Grade 4’ if AETOXGR='4';

Pooled grouping of toxicity grade for analysis: 
<3 when .<ATOXGRN <3;
>=3 when ATOXGRN >=3;

If MDOSREF='Vaccination 1',  set to:
'Placebo' if EX.EXTRT='PLACEBO' where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 1' ;
'mRNA-1273 50 ug' if EX.EXTRT='mRNA-1273' and 0<EXDOSE<=75 where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 1'; 
'mRNA-1273 100 ug' if EX.EXTRT='mRNA-1273' and EXDOSE>75 where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 1';
if MDOSREF='Vaccination 2',  set to:
'Placebo' if EX.EXTRT='PLACEBO' where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 29' ;
'mRNA-1273 50 ug' if EX.EXTRT='mRNA-1273' and 0<EXDOSE<=75 where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 29';
'mRNA-1273 100 ug' if EX.EXTRT='mRNA-1273' and EXDOSE>75 where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 29';

Set to 'Grade 0' if FASTRESC='NONE'  or FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 0'
Set to 'Grade 1' if FASTRESC= 'NO INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY' or contains 'GRADE 1';
Set to 'Grade 2' if FASTRESC= 'SOME INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY NOT REQUIRING MEDICAL ATTENTION' or contains 'GRADE 2';
Set to 'Grade 3' if FASTRESC= 'PREVENTS DAILY ACTIVITY AND REQUIRES MEDICAL ATTENTION' or contains 'GRADE 3';
Set to 'Grade 4' if FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 4'

Grade 1 if AVALC= ‘NO INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY or contains 'GRADE 1'’;
Grade 2 if AVALC= ‘SOME INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY NOT REQUIRING MEDICAL ATTENTION’ or contains 'GRADE 2';
Grade 3 if AVALC= ‘PREVENTS DAILY ACTIVITY AND REQUIRES MEDICAL ATTENTION’ or contains 'GRADE 3';
Grade 4 if AVALC contains 'GRADE 4'

Grade 1 if AVALC= 'NO INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY' or contains 'GRADE 1';
Grade 2 if AVALC= ‘SOME INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 2';
Grade 3 if AVALC= ‘SIGNIFICANT; PREVENTS DAILY ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 3';
Grade 4 if AVALC contains 'GRADE 4'

Grade 1 if AVALC=’NO INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY or contains 'GRADE 1'’;
Grade 2 if AVALC= ‘REPEATED USE OF OVER-THE-COUNTER PAIN RELIEVER > 24 HOURS OR SOME INTERFERERENCE WITH ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 2';
Grade 3 if AVALC= ‘ANY USE OF PRESCRIPTION PAIN RELIEVER OR PREVENTS DAILY ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 3';
Grade 4 if AVALC contains 'GRADE 4'

Grade 1 if AVALC= ‘NO INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY OR 1-2 EPISODES/24 HOURS’ or contains 'GRADE 1';
Grade 2 if AVALC= ‘SOME INTERFERENCE WITH ACTIVITY OR >2 EPISODES/24 HOURS’ or contains 'GRADE 2';
Grade 3 if AVALC= ‘PREVENTS DAILY ACTIVITY, REQUIRES OUTPATIENT IV HYDRATION’ or contains 'GRADE 3';
Grade 4 if AVALC contains 'GRADE 4'

Grade 1 if AVALC=’DOES NOT INTERFERE WITH ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 1';
Grade 2 if AVALC= ‘REPEATED USE OF OVER-THE-COUNTER PAIN RELIEVER > 24 HOURS OR INTERFERES WITH ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 2';
Grade 3 if AVALC= ‘ANY USE OF PRESCRIPTION PAIN RELIEVER OR PREVENTS DAILY ACTIVITY’ or contains 'GRADE 3';
Grade 4 if AVALC contains 'GRADE 4'

Set to corresponding FAAE.FASTRESN based on corresponding AVALC if the record is from FAAE IF PARAMCD in (ERYTHDIA,
SWELLDIA);
Set to corresponding VS.VSSTRESN based on corresponding AVALC if the record is from VS if PARAMCD=FEVER

Set to 'Grade 0' if FASTRESC=’NONE’  or FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 0'
Set to 'Grade 1' if FASTRESC='DOES NOT INTERFERE WITH ACTIVITY' or contains 'GRADE 1';
Set to 'Grade 2' if FASTRESC='REPEATED USE OF OVER-THE-COUNTER PAIN RELIEVER > 24 HOURS OR INTERFERES WITH ACTIVITY' or contains 'GRADE 2';
Set to 'Grade 3' if FASTRESC='ANY USE OF PRESCRIPTION PAIN RELIEVER OR PREVENTS DAILY ACTIVITY' or contains 'GRADE 3'
Set to 'Grade 4' if FASTRESC contains 'GRADE 4'

Set to 'Grade 0' if FASTRESC='GRADE 0 = NO RASH' or contains 'GRADE 0';
Set to 'Grade 1' if FASTRESC='GRADE 1 = LOCALIZED RASH, WITHOUT ASSOCIATED SYMPTOMS' or contains 'GRADE 1';
Set to 'Grade 2' if FASTRESC='GRADE 2 = MACULOPAPULAR RASH, COVERING 50% BODY SURFACE AREA WITH URTICARIA' or contains 'GRADE 2';
Set to 'Grade 3' if FASTRESC='GRADE 3 = GENERALIZED URTICARIAL, COVERING 50% BODY SURFACE AREA' or contains 'GRADE 3';
Set to 'Grade 4' if FASTRESC='GRADE 4 = GENERALIZED EXFOLIATIVE, ULCERATIVE OR BULLOUS DERMATITIS, E.G. STEVENS-JOHNSON SYNDROME OR ERYTHEMA MULTIFORME' or contains 'GRADE 4';

Set to numeric date part of CM.CMENDTC if day, month, and year are all present

If day and month are both missing, AENDT is whichever is earliest of the following: 
31DECYYYY, EOSDT, or DTHDT;
If only day is missing, AENDT is whichiever is earliest of the following: EOSDT, DTHDT, or xxMMMYYYY where xx is the last day of the month;
blank otherwise

Convert date part of CM.CMSTDTC to numeric if day, month, and year are all present;
-If only DAY is missing:
If the CM end date (CMENDTC) is after the date of first vaccination (ADSL.TR01SDT) or is missing AND the start month and year of the CM (CMSTDTC) coincide with the start month and year of the first vaccination (ADSL.TR01SDT), use the date of first vaccination; 
Otherwise, use the first day of the month;
-If DAY and Month are both missing:
If the CM end date is after the date of first vaccination or is missing AND the start year of the CM coincides with the start year of the first vaccination, use the date of first vaccination
Otherwise, use the first day of the year;
-If DAY, Month and Year are all missing, the date will not be imputed. blank otherwise
Note: if CMENDTC is partial:
If only day is missing, month and year coincide with or after the month and year of TR01SDT, treat CMENDTC as after TR01SDT, otherwise treat CMENDTC as before TR01SDT.
If month is missing (regardless of day is missing or not), if year coincides with or after the year of TR01SDT, treat CMENDTC as after TR01SDT, otherwise treat CMENDTC as before TR01SDT.
If year is missing (regardles of day and month),  treat CMENDTC as after TR01SDT.

'Y' If  CMDECOD contains 
'PARACETAMOL', 'DIPHENHYDRAMINE HYDROCHLORIDE;PARACETAMOL', 'IBUPROFEN', 'DIPHENHYDRAMINE CITRATE;IBUPROFEN', 'DIPHENHYDRAMINE HYDROCHLORIDE', 'IBUPROFEN', 
'NAPROXEN SODIUM', 'DEXTROMETHORPHAN HYDROBROMIDE', 'GUAIFENESIN', 'PARACETAMOL;PSEUDOEPHEDRINE HYDROCHLORIDE';
'DEXTROMETHORPHAN HYDROBROMIDE;DOXYLAMINE SUCCINATE;EPHEDRINE SULFATE;ETHANOL;PARACETAMOL';
'ACETYLSALICYLIC ACID;CAFFEINE;PARACETAMOL'

Set to 'Y' if (ASTDT <= TR01EDT + 28 days) and (AENDT >= TR01SDT or AENDT is missing); or 
if ASTDT is missing and (AENDT >= TR01SDT or AENDT is missing); 
missing otherwise

FAOT.FASTRESC if source data are from FAOT; 
ER.EROCCUR if source data are from ER; 
SS.SSSTRESC if source data are from SS; 
Set to numeric part of ER.ERDUR for PARAMCD=DUR and convert to character

If VISIT doesn't contain 'Unsched', set to 'Day xx' part of VISIT,
If ADY>1 and VISIT contains 'Unsched', set AVISIT as follows: using the visit window below:
If VISIT with 1<ADY<=11, then AVISIT = 'Day 8', 
else if VISIT with 12<=ADY<=22, then AVISIT = 'Day 15', 
else if VISIT with 23<=ADY<=32, then AVISIT = 'Day 29', 
else if VISIT with 33<=ADY<=39, then AVISIT = 'Day 36', 
else if VISIT with 40<=ADY<=50, then AVISIT = 'Day 43', 
else if VISIT with 51<=ADY<=133, then AVISIT = 'Day 57', 
else if VISIT with 134=<ADY<=301, then AVISIT = 'Day 209', 
else if VISIT with ADY>=302, then AVISIT = 'Day 394',
After the steps above, sort data by AVISITN and ADY, set the unscheduled visit (i.e., VISIT contains 'Unsched') records to blank if AVISITN >any previous AVISITN AND ADY<=any previous ADY). For example, Scheduled Day 36 is with AVISITN=6 (Day 36) and ADY=42 and an unscheduled visit is with AVISITN=7 (Day 43) and ADY=40, set AVISIT to blank for this unscheduled visit

If ABLFL='Y' then AVISIT='Baseline';
if ADY>1 and VISIT doesn't contain "UNSCHEDULE", set to 'Day xx' part of VISIT;  ; 
if ADY>1 and VISIT contains "UNSCHED", set AVISIT as follows: using the visit window below:
If VISIT with 1<ADY<=22, then AVISIT = ’Day 15’; 
else if VISIT with 23<=ADY<=36, then AVISIT = ’Day 29’; 
else if VISIT with 37<=ADY<=50, then AVISIT = ’Day 43’; 
else if VISIT with 51<=ADY<=133, then AVISIT = ’Day 57’; 
else if VISIT with 134=<ADY<=301, then AVISIT = ’Day 209’; 
else if VISIT with ADY>=302, then AVISIT = ’Day 394’;

For PARCAT1='Serum SARS-CoV-2 Neutralizing Antibodies', set to ISTEST; 
For PARCAT1='Serum SARS-CoV-2 Binding Antibodies', if PARAMCD does not contain 'L10' then set to ISTEST " (" ||ISSTRESU|| ")" if ISSTRESU is non-missing for the test, or ISTEST if ISSTRESU is not available for the test; 
If PARAMCD contains 'L10' then assign PARAM based on PARAMCD: 
'LOG10(PsVNT50)' if PARAMCD='L10PVN50'; 
'LOG10(PsVNT80)' if PARAMCD='L10PVN80'; 
'LOG10(MN50)' if PARAMCD='L10MN50'; 
'LOG10(VAC58 Spike IgG Antibody)' if PARAMCD='LV58IGGS'
'LOG10(VAC58 Nucleocapsid IgG Antibody)' if PARAMCD='LV58IGGN'；
'LOG10(VAC58 Spike IgM Antibody)' if PARAMCD='LV58IGMS'；
'LOG10(VAC58 Spike IgG subclass 1)' if PARAMCD='LV58IG1S'；
'LOG10(VAC58 Spike IgG subclass 2)' if PARAMCD='LV58IG2S'；
'LOG10(VAC58 Spike IgG subclass 3)' if PARAMCD='LV58IG3S'；
'LOG10(VAC58 Spike IgG subclass 4)' if PARAMCD='LV58IG4S'

Set to PARAMCD ||' <2 x ULN' if CRIT1FL='Y' and PARAMCD in (ALP); 
Set to PARAMCD ||' >=2 x ULN' if CRIT1FL='Y' and PARAMCD in (BILI); 
Set to PARAMCD ||' >3 x ULN' if CRIT1FL='Y' and PARAMCD in (ALT, AST)

Set to 'Y' if If AVAL/ANRHI <2 and PARAMCD =ALP;
Set to 'Y' if If AVAL/ANRHI >=2 and PARAMCD =BILI;
Set to 'Y' if If AVAL/ANRHI >3 and PARAMCD in (ALT, AST);

If (.<ADSL.TR01SDTM<=ADTM <ADSL.DOS2DTM) or (.<ADSL.TR01SDTM<=ADTM and ADSL.DOS2DTM is missing), set to 'Vaccination 1';
if .<ADSL.DOS2DTM<=ADTM, set to  'Vaccination 2'; 
use date variables for comparison when time part is not available

"If ABLFL='Y' then AVISIT='Baseline';
if ADY>1 and VISITNUM is 5, 8, set to 'Day xx' part of VISIT;  ; 
if ADY>1 and VISITNUM is not 5, 8, set AVISIT as follows: using the visit window below:
If VISIT with 2<=ADY<=43, then AVISIT = ’Day 29’; 
else if VISIT with 44<=ADY<=70, then AVISIT = ’Day 57’; 
else if VISIT with 71<=ADY, then AVISIT = ’Day 71 or Beyond’; "

'Based on AGE: 
'>=18 and <=22 Years' if 18<=AGE<=22';  
'>=23 and <=25 Years' if 23<=AGE<=25';  
'>25 and <55 Years' if 25<AGE<55'; 
'>=55 Years' if COHORT contains 'COHORT 2'

Set to 'Y' if both criteria met:
1. SAFFL='Y'; 
2. Have at least one non-missing FAORRES where FATPTREF = 'DOSE 1' in FACE OR have at least one non-missing VSORRES where VSTPTREF = 'DOSE 1' and VSTEST contains "Temperature" where VSCAT contains "REACTOGENICITY" in VS; 
Set to 'N' otherwise.

Set to 'Y' if all criteria met:
1. SAFFL='Y'; 
2. Have at least one non-missing FAORRES where FATPTREF = 'DOSE 2' in FACE OR have at least one non-missing VSORRES where VSTPTREF = 'DOSE 2' and VSTEST contains "Temperature" where VSCAT contains "REACTOGENICITY" in VS; 
3. DOSE2FL='Y'; 
Set to 'N' otherwise

Set to:
'Fever' if PARAMCD = 'TEMP';
'Tachycardia' if PARAMCD = 'PULSE';
'Systolic Hypertension' if PARAMCD = 'SYSBP';
'Diastolic Hypertension' if PARAMCD = 'DIABP';
'Respiratory Rate Increased' if PARAMCD = 'RESP'.

Set to
'Bradycardia' if PARAMCD = 'PULSE';
Hypotension' if PARAMCD = 'SYSBP'

If ABLFL='Y', then AVISIT = 'Baseline',
if VISIT=Visit 1 Day 1 and VSTPT='POST DOSE' then AVISIT='Day 1',
if ADY>1 and VISIT doesn't contain 'Unsched', set to 'Day xx' part of VISIT,  
if ADY>1 and VISIT contains 'Unsched', set AVISIT as follows: using the visit window below:
If VISIT with 1<ADY<=11, then AVISIT = 'Day 8', 
else if VISIT with 12<=ADY<=22, then AVISIT = 'Day 15', 
else if VISIT with 23<=ADY<=32, then AVISIT = 'Day 29', 
else if VISIT with 33<=ADY<=39, then AVISIT = 'Day 36', 
else if VISIT with 40<=ADY<=50, then AVISIT = 'Day 43', 
else if VISIT with 51<=ADY<=133, then AVISIT = 'Day 57', 
else if VISIT with 134=<ADY<=301, then AVISIT = 'Day 209', 
else if VISIT with ADY>=302, then AVISIT = 'Day 394',
After the steps above, sort data by AVISITN and ADY, set the unscheduled visit (i.e., VISIT contains 'Unsched') records to blank if AVISITN >any previous AVISITN AND ADY<=any previous ADY). For example, Scheduled Day 36 is with AVISITN=6 (Day 36) and ADY=42 and an unscheduled visit is with AVISITN=7 (Day 43) and ADY=40, set AVISIT to blank for this unscheduled visit

If (.<ADSL.TR01SDTM<=ADTM <ADSL.DOS2DTM) or (.<ADSL.TR01SDTM<=ADTM and ADSL.DOS2DTM is missing), set to 'Vaccination 1';
if .<ADSL.DOS2DTM<=ADTM, set to  'Vaccination 2'; 
use date variables for comparison when time part is not available

Set to 0 If CHG=0 ;
else set to (CHG/BASE)*100 if BASE ne 0 , 
otherwise set to missing

"If (.<ADSL.TR01SDTM<=ADTM <DOS2DTM) or (.<ADSL.TR01SDTM<=ADTM and ADSL.DOS2DTM is missing):
'Placebo' if EX.EXTRT='PLACEBO' where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 1' ;
'mRNA-1273 50 ug' if EX.EXTRT='mRNA-1273' and 
1) 0<EXDOSE<=75 where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 1', or 
2) EXDOSTXT contains '>0-25', '>25-<50' or '>50-75' where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 1'; 
'mRNA-1273 100 ug' if EX.EXTRT='mRNA-1273' and 
1) EXDOSE>75 where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 1', or 
2) EXDOSTXT contains '>75-<100' or '>100-125' or '>125' where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 1';  if .<ADSL.DOS2DTM<=ASTDTM:
'Placebo' if EX.EXTRT='PLACEBO' where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 29' ;
'mRNA-1273 50 ug' if 
1) EX.EXTRT='mRNA-1273' and 0<EXDOSE<=75 where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 29', or 
2) EXDOSTXT contains '>0-25', '>25-<50' or '>50-75' where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 29';  
'mRNA-1273 100 ug' if EX.EXTRT='mRNA-1273' and 
1) EXDOSE>75 where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 29', or
2) EXDOSTXT contains '>75-<100' or '>100-125' or '>125' where EX.VISIT contains 'Day 29'; 
if time part of ADTM, TR01SDTM, or DOS2DTM is missing, use ADT, TR01SDT, and DOSE2DT to replace ADTM, TR01SDTM, and DOS2DTM, respectively."

“<=1 Pre-dose" for ‘Baseline’
“Day 2 – Day 22” for 'Day 15'; 
“Day 23 – Day 36” for 'Day 29';  
“Day 37 – Day 50” for 'Day 43'; 
“Day 51 – Day 133” for 'Day 57';
